docs.lead_paragraph: At the ninth hole, Vijay Singh thought he was out of the HP Classic. At the 18th, he knew the tournament was his for the taking. Singh made a 25-foot birdie at No. 18 Monday to win the rain-delayed tournament, denying the Masters champion Phil Mickelson his second straight victory and Joe Ogilvie his first title.
